Command.script:
this.pause()
this.changeText('Here is another node. And we have connected them via WebSockets.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('The concept of node is a bit abstract. Let\'s turn them into server and client.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Now imagine we have this object on the server. Client can subscribe.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('When client subscribe, this will receive a copy of the object.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('What happen if server mutate the object?')

this.pause()
this.changeText('When the server mutates the object this sends the mutation to all the subscribers. So now we have client and server up to date.')

this.pause()
this.changeText('Now is the client who wants to mutate the object. What happen then?')
this.pause() this.changeText('When client mutates the object, server will not receive the mutation. But why?')

this.pause() this.changeText('Mutations are unidirectional. Remember this, because is the principle of this protocol. Only the owner of the object will emit mutations to subscribers. Server is the owner in this case.')

this.pause() this.changeText('Distributed Object Protocol allows us to call remote functions (RPC). So what we can do, is define a function on the server. And this function will be available on the client.')
